73
00:02:37,480 --> 00:02:37,960
a coin.

74
00:02:37,960 --> 00:02:40,500
Lay a coin down on the table,

75
00:02:40,500 --> 00:02:41,820
I don't have a coin

76
00:02:41,820 --> 00:02:43,140
so we'll take this coffee top

77
00:02:43,140 --> 00:02:43,460
here,

78
00:02:43,460 --> 00:02:45,100
I could put it down heads

79
00:02:45,100 --> 00:02:46,740
or I could put it down tails.

80
00:02:46,740 --> 00:02:48,200
I doubt if you can tell

81
00:02:48,200 --> 00:02:49,230
the difference from where you're sitting

82
00:02:49,230 --> 00:02:50,260
but I can tell the difference,

83
00:02:50,260 --> 00:02:51,700
this is heads,

84
00:02:51,960 --> 00:02:52,700
that's tails.

85
00:02:52,700 --> 00:02:54,870
So we have a system

86
00:02:54,870 --> 00:02:57,040
then that's characterized by two systems,

87
00:02:57,040 --> 00:02:57,040
the first one

88
00:02:57,040 --> 00:02:57,280
is a state,

89
00:02:57,280 --> 00:02:57,640
the second one is a state of being,

90
00:02:57,640 --> 00:02:57,640
and the third one is a state of evolution.

91
00:02:57,640 --> 00:02:57,640
So we have two states,

92
00:02:57,640 --> 00:03:01,370
two states of being and we want

93
00:03:01,370 --> 00:03:05,100
to add to those two states a law,

94
00:03:05,140 --> 00:03:07,930
a law of evolution in going from one

95
00:03:07,930 --> 00:03:10,720
instant of time to the next instant of time,

96
00:03:10,720 --> 00:03:11,020
from

97
00:03:11,020 --> 00:03:13,780
one beat of the stroboscopic light to the next one.

98
00:03:13,780 --> 00:03:17,100
What kind of laws are allowable,

99
00:03:17,220 --> 00:03:20,040
what kind of laws do the basic principles

100
00:03:20,040 --> 00:03:22,860
of physics allow and what kind of laws don't

101
00:03:22,860 --> 00:03:23,240
they allow?

102
00:03:23,240 --> 00:03:25,580
That's going to be our

103
00:03:25,580 --> 00:03:27,920
first kind of question for tonight.

104
00:03:44,000 --> 00:03:48,500
So our first concept is the space of states,

105
00:03:48,500 --> 00:03:51,200
in this case just heads and tails,

106
00:03:51,200 --> 00:03:52,240
it's just

107
00:03:52,860 --> 00:03:53,060
two points,

108
00:03:53,060 --> 00:03:54,760
heads and tails,

109
00:03:54,760 --> 00:03:56,460
so two points in an abstract space,

110
00:03:56,460 --> 00:03:58,860
heads and tails.

111
00:03:58,860 --> 00:04:02,260
It's

112
00:04:02,260 --> 00:04:03,300
called the phase space,

113
00:04:03,300 --> 00:04:05,900
it's called the phase space of a system,

114
00:04:05,900 --> 00:04:07,440
the space of possible states

115
00:04:07,440 --> 00:04:08,080
of a system.

116
00:04:08,080 --> 00:04:09,500
And what do I mean

117
00:04:09,500 --> 00:04:10,920
by a state of a system?

118
00:04:10,920 --> 00:04:12,520
I mean everything that you need

119
00:04:12,520 --> 00:04:15,420
to know in order to predict what happens next,

120
00:04:15,420 --> 00:04:18,800
everything you need to know in order to be

121
00:04:18,800 --> 00:04:20,260
able to say with certainty what the

122
00:04:20,260 --> 00:04:21,720
next state of the system will be.

123
00:04:22,860 --> 00:04:25,300
So that's called the phase space of the system,

124
00:04:25,300 --> 00:04:27,620
in this case just heads and tails.

125
00:04:27,620 --> 00:04:29,460
What kind

126
00:04:29,460 --> 00:04:31,220
of laws can you imagine,

127
00:04:31,220 --> 00:04:32,670
what kind of laws of nature

128
00:04:32,670 --> 00:04:34,120
can you imagine for this extremely

129
00:04:34,120 --> 00:04:35,100
simple world?

130
00:04:35,100 --> 00:04:37,080
It is the simplest—well,

131
00:04:37,080 --> 00:04:39,420
I suppose you could imagine a slightly simpler

132
00:04:39,420 --> 00:04:39,900
world.

133
00:04:39,900 --> 00:04:42,420
You can imagine a world with only one state,

134
00:04:42,420 --> 00:04:43,260
heads.

135
00:04:43,260 --> 00:04:45,780
Not much can happen in that

136
00:04:45,780 --> 00:04:46,020
world.

137
00:04:46,020 --> 00:04:47,440
There's only one law of physics.

138
00:04:47,440 --> 00:04:49,520
Heads go to heads,

139
00:04:49,520 --> 00:04:51,600
and heads go to heads go to heads.

140
00:04:51,600 --> 00:04:52,880
that's extremely boring,

141
00:04:52,880 --> 00:04:54,060
nothing ever happens,

142
00:04:54,060 --> 00:04:55,140
because there's only one state,

143
00:04:55,140 --> 00:04:55,700
so how could

144
00:04:55,700 --> 00:04:56,300
anything happen?

145
00:04:56,300 --> 00:04:58,140
But with two states,

146
00:04:58,140 --> 00:04:58,840
heads and tails,

147
00:04:58,840 --> 00:05:01,520
you can have a richer variety of possible

148
00:05:01,520 --> 00:05:02,360
laws of physics.

149
00:05:02,360 --> 00:05:04,080
One law,

150
00:05:04,080 --> 00:05:06,020
let's take the various varieties of

151
00:05:06,020 --> 00:05:07,960
laws of physics we could have,

152
00:05:08,480 --> 00:05:10,280
one law might just say,

153
00:05:10,280 --> 00:05:12,740
you stay the same.

154
00:05:12,740 --> 00:05:15,020
If the state of the system

155
00:05:15,020 --> 00:05:17,300
is heads at one instant of

156
00:05:17,300 --> 00:05:17,420
time,

157
00:05:17,420 --> 00:05:20,000
then the next instant of time it will be heads.

158
00:05:20,000 --> 00:05:22,040
If it starts tails,

159
00:05:22,040 --> 00:05:23,580
it will stay tails.

160
00:05:24,180 --> 00:05:25,620
That's a very boring law,

161
00:05:25,620 --> 00:05:29,180
and let's graph that law by drawing an arrow.

162
00:05:29,180 --> 00:05:30,800
If it starts heads,

163
00:05:31,600 --> 00:05:33,160
then it stays heads.

164
00:05:33,160 --> 00:05:35,830
Let's just represent that by drawing

165
00:05:35,830 --> 00:05:38,500
an arrow from head to head,

166
00:05:38,600 --> 00:05:39,880
and from tail to tail.

167
00:05:39,880 --> 00:05:41,680
The meaning of this arrow,

168
00:05:41,680 --> 00:05:43,620
you start at the tail end of the arrow,

169
00:05:43,740 --> 00:05:45,200
and you follow it,

170
00:05:45,200 --> 00:05:46,240
and you see that it

171
00:05:46,240 --> 00:05:47,280
comes around to the same point.

172
00:05:48,060 --> 00:05:50,230
That stands for the rule that

173
00:05:50,230 --> 00:05:52,400
says that a heads stays a heads,

174
00:05:52,400 --> 00:05:53,800
and in this case,

175
00:05:53,900 --> 00:05:55,000
a tail stays a tail.

176
00:05:55,000 --> 00:05:57,060
So this is a very dull law of nature.

177
00:05:57,060 --> 00:06:00,200
This stays that way for endless amounts

178
00:06:00,200 --> 00:06:00,800
of time,

179
00:06:00,800 --> 00:06:05,480
and this stays that way for endless amounts of time.

180
00:06:05,480 --> 00:06:08,560
Another possible law of nature

181
00:06:08,560 --> 00:06:14,920
would be a slightly more interesting situation.

182
00:06:14,920 --> 00:06:17,280
If you look at it at one instant of time,

183
00:06:17,300 --> 00:06:18,480
the next instant,

184
00:06:18,480 --> 00:06:19,160
it's the opposite.

185
00:06:19,160 --> 00:06:20,720
Heads goes to tails,

186
00:06:20,720 --> 00:06:21,480
goes to heads,

187
00:06:21,480 --> 00:06:22,260
goes to tails.

188
00:06:22,600 --> 00:06:24,620
These are deterministic laws.

189
00:06:24,620 --> 00:06:27,160
Deterministic laws mean that if you

190
00:06:27,160 --> 00:06:29,700
know what is happening at one

191
00:06:29,700 --> 00:06:30,040
instant,

192
00:06:30,040 --> 00:06:32,000
you know forever after.

193
00:06:32,000 --> 00:06:36,120
You know everything about the system infinitely into

194
00:06:36,120 --> 00:06:36,600
the future.

195
00:06:36,600 --> 00:06:38,700
Completely deterministic.

196
00:06:38,700 --> 00:06:40,980
Classical mechanics has that nature to it,

197
00:06:40,980 --> 00:06:41,660
that it is

198
00:06:41,660 --> 00:06:43,060
completely deterministic.

199
00:06:43,400 --> 00:06:44,960
You know the adversals?

200
00:06:45,200 --> 00:06:45,440
No.

201
00:06:46,080 --> 00:06:46,720
No.

202
00:06:47,300 --> 00:06:48,800
The adversals is in a certain sense always reversible,

203
00:06:48,800 --> 00:06:50,100
but we're coming to that.

204
00:06:50,640 --> 00:06:51,200
All right,

205
00:06:51,200 --> 00:06:53,670
so to draw the graph representing heads

206
00:06:53,670 --> 00:06:56,140
goes to tails and tails goes to heads,

207
00:06:56,640 --> 00:06:58,630
we draw an arrow from heads

208
00:06:58,630 --> 00:07:00,620
