00:44:59,000 --> 00:44:59,200
Tails,

1487
00:44:59,200 --> 00:44:59,200
heads goes to heads,

1488
00:44:59,200 --> 00:44:59,200
tails.

1489
00:44:59,640 --> 00:45:00,980
So that goes here.

1490
00:45:01,560 --> 00:45:02,740
That goes to tails,

1491
00:45:02,740 --> 00:45:02,980
tails.

1492
00:45:03,160 --> 00:45:04,060
Change the third one.

1493
00:45:05,860 --> 00:45:07,640
It seems to me we should

1494
00:45:07,640 --> 00:45:09,420
be able to make a consistent law.

1495
00:45:12,820 --> 00:45:13,300
What?

1496
00:45:15,440 --> 00:45:16,400
This one?

1497
00:45:17,040 --> 00:45:18,000
This one.

1498
00:45:19,140 --> 00:45:19,620
Oh,

1499
00:45:19,620 --> 00:45:20,060
tails,

1500
00:45:20,060 --> 00:45:21,580
tails goes to tails,

1501
00:45:21,580 --> 00:45:21,940
tails goes to tails.

1502
00:45:22,080 --> 00:45:22,560
Tails,

1503
00:45:22,560 --> 00:45:23,080
tails goes to tails,

1504
00:45:23,080 --> 00:45:23,080
tails goes to tails.

1505
00:45:23,100 --> 00:45:23,140
Tails,

1506
00:45:23,140 --> 00:45:23,400
tails goes to heads.

1507
00:45:24,020 --> 00:45:24,500
Yeah,

1508
00:45:24,500 --> 00:45:24,820
OK.

1509
00:45:25,180 --> 00:45:26,220
So then tails,

1510
00:45:26,220 --> 00:45:27,320
tails goes to heads.

1511
00:45:28,280 --> 00:45:30,760
And that means that tails,

1512
00:45:30,760 --> 00:45:31,160
tails,

1513
00:45:31,160 --> 00:45:31,660
heads.

1514
00:45:32,060 --> 00:45:33,000
So that means tails,

1515
00:45:33,000 --> 00:45:34,040
tails goes to tails,

1516
00:45:34,040 --> 00:45:34,780
heads.

1517
00:45:36,060 --> 00:45:36,540
Ah.

1518
00:45:37,540 --> 00:45:38,020
Oh,

1519
00:45:38,020 --> 00:45:38,340
OK,

1520
00:45:38,340 --> 00:45:38,560
good,

1521
00:45:38,560 --> 00:45:38,760
good.

1522
00:45:38,920 --> 00:45:40,220
Now we have a workable law.

1523
00:45:40,820 --> 00:45:42,300
Now we have a workable law.

1524
00:45:42,580 --> 00:45:44,860
The only thing we had to do was

1525
00:45:44,860 --> 00:45:47,140
to say that what we originally called a configuration,

1526
00:45:47,940 --> 00:45:49,580
namely a single heads or tails,

1527
00:45:49,580 --> 00:45:52,440
was not a complete specification.

1528
00:45:52,440 --> 00:45:56,200
A complete specification of information

1529
00:45:56,200 --> 00:45:59,960
involved two pieces of information.

1530
00:46:00,360 --> 00:46:02,280
And once we recognized that,

1531
00:46:02,280 --> 00:46:05,890
we were able to write this

1532
00:46:05,890 --> 00:46:09,500
down as a law of physics,

1533
00:46:09,720 --> 00:46:12,180
which is deterministic and reversible.

1534
00:46:13,480 --> 00:46:14,080
OK.

1535
00:46:14,380 --> 00:46:16,060
So you don't know offhand.

1536
00:46:16,200 --> 00:46:18,930
You don't know to begin with what pieces of information you

1537
00:46:18,930 --> 00:46:21,660
need to know in order to know what to do next.

1538
00:46:23,040 --> 00:46:25,680
But that's what the configuration space,

1539
00:46:25,680 --> 00:46:27,240
or that's what the phase space is.

1540
00:46:27,460 --> 00:46:29,360
It's the collection of all the things you

1541
00:46:29,360 --> 00:46:31,260
need to know to know what happens next.

1542
00:46:31,660 --> 00:46:32,100
Now,

1543
00:46:32,100 --> 00:46:32,380
of course,

1544
00:46:32,380 --> 00:46:33,300
you could go beyond this.

1545
00:46:33,600 --> 00:46:34,380
You could say,

1546
00:46:34,380 --> 00:46:36,280
I need to know the first three

1547
00:46:36,280 --> 00:46:38,180
things in order to know what happens next.

1548
00:46:38,700 --> 00:46:39,520
You can do that.

1549
00:46:39,760 --> 00:46:41,500
You'll simply need more states

1550
00:46:41,500 --> 00:46:43,240
to make a deterministic system.

1551
00:46:47,060 --> 00:46:49,350
What would it mean in classical mechanics to

1552
00:46:49,350 --> 00:46:51,640
need more information than the positions of the tails?

1553
00:46:51,640 --> 00:46:52,280
Or the positions and velocities?

1554
00:46:54,400 --> 00:46:55,700
Suppose you needed the positions,

1555
00:46:55,700 --> 00:46:56,280
velocities,

1556
00:46:56,280 --> 00:46:57,220
and accelerations.

1557
00:46:58,920 --> 00:47:00,740
That would mean third order differential equations,

1558
00:47:00,740 --> 00:47:02,420
but what would it say about the phase space?

1559
00:47:04,860 --> 00:47:06,580
It would mean you would need positions,

1560
00:47:06,580 --> 00:47:07,340
velocities,

1561
00:47:07,340 --> 00:47:10,220
and accelerations to represent the phase space.

1562
00:47:12,180 --> 00:47:13,520
As it happens,

1563
00:47:13,520 --> 00:47:16,920
that is not the case for classical mechanics.

1564
00:47:17,660 --> 00:47:19,040
That's an experimental fact.

1565
00:47:22,480 --> 00:47:24,680
But it wouldn't stop us if we did.

1566
00:47:24,820 --> 00:47:26,580
If we did need the accelerations,

1567
00:47:26,580 --> 00:47:28,240
we would just write third order equations,

1568
00:47:28,500 --> 00:47:30,800
and we would make our phase space three-dimensional.

